T1	Participants 647 780	The results indicated that acute exercise facilitated performance in the Stroop Test, particularly in the Stroop Color-Word condition
T2	Participants 270 349	Forty children with ADHD were randomly assigned into exercise or control groups
T3	Participants 107 268	This study was conducted to determine the effect of acute aerobic exercise on executive function in children with attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD)
T4	Participants 1013 1217	Tentative explanations for the exercise effect postulate that exercise allocates attention resources, influences the dorsolateral prefrontal cortex, and is implicated in exercise-induced dopamine release.
